observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Acting Municipal Mayor:

a. designate an official focal person for the program who will ensure compliance of the Management with the deed of donation and deployment plan, and handle the operations of the program;

b. seek authority from the Sangguniang Bayan before the execution of the purchase agreements with the PNOs;

c. in coordination with the Municipal Engineer, direct the designated focal person to conduct a thorough inventory and appraisal of all the E-trike vehicles and subsequently submit a report to the Municipal Accountant for recognition of the write-down of the E-trike vehicles for its fair presentation in the financial statements; and

d. consider revisiting the deployment plan and conduct consultations with the PNOs to come up with viable guidelines for the program.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Acting Municipal Mayor:

a. direct the Municipal Accountant to provide a copy of the Registry of Public Infrastructures to the Audit Team for reference in the reversion of the infrastructure assets to the Road Network account;

b. instruct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for all road projects of the Municipality to facilitate proper recording thereof in the books;

c. require the (i) General Services Officer to submit the Report on the Local Road Network and (ii) the Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of its road networks in order to ascertain the existence of the Road Networks accounts; and

d. mandate the Municipal Assessor, Municipal Engineer and MPDC to determine the road lots of the Municipal Road Networks. Thereafter, the Municipal Assessor and the MPDC revalidate and verify any third-party claims on the road lots before the Municipal Accountant finally recognize the same in the books for the fair presentation of the financial statements inclusive of the Road Network account.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor:

instruct the Municipal Assessor and the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to revalidate and verify any third party claims on the road lots. Thereafter, require the Municipal Assessor (i) to submit the certification of the total Land Holdings of the Municipality, including the Road Lots, to the Municipal Accountant for the recognition of the ROW in the books of accounts; and (ii) to furnish the Audit Team copy of the same report; 

instruct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for all road projects of the Municipality to facilitate proper recording in the books. 

We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant provide a copy of the Registry of Public Infrastructures to the Audit Team for reference in the reversion of the infrastructure assets to the Road Network account;

enjoin the compliance of the Municipal Accountant, GSO, Municipal Engineer, MPDC, Municipal Assessor and the Inventory Committee to comply with the requirements of COA Circular 2015-008 particularly on their respective duties and responsibilities; and

require the (i) General Services Officer to submit the Report on the Local Road Network; and (ii) the Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of its road networks in order to ascertain the existence of the Road Networks accounts.

We recommended that the:

Municipal Mayor (i) secure Environmental Compliance Certificate from the DENR-EMB in conformity with P.D. No. 1586; 



(ii) direct the MEEDO and the Municipal Health Officer to inspect the slaughterhouse and make necessary corrections and orientation of the site personnel on proper and hygienic handling of food animals in conformity with the Code on Sanitation of the Philippines; (iii) introduce improvements to the facilities of the slaughterhouse in accordance with the national hygiene and sanitation standards, and eventually secure the accreditation of the slaughterhouse, if warranted, otherwise construct a new slaughterhouse; and (iv) direct the MEEDO and the Municipal Engineer to inspect and reassess the existing facilities of the Jalal slaughterhouse and propose a budget to make it operational;

MEEDO cause the implementation of a humane way of slaughtering food animals in compliance with the Animal Welfare Act of 1998; and

Building Official conduct an ocular inspection of the existing slaughterhouse and submit the corresponding report to the MEEDO/ Municipal Mayor on the assessment on the integrity of the structure as basis for decision making.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor: 

instruct the MSWDO to (i) strictly abide by the guidelines in the granting of financial assistance taking into consideration the noted deficiencies in audit; 

(ii) establish a database of assistance granted to monitor its frequency; 

(iii) thoroughly screen/interview the clients to properly address his/her concerns;
(iv) require complete documentary requirements from the client before the release of assistance; and

(v) refrain from accommodating financial assistance facilitated by the Legislative personnel and prospectively, advise all clients to directly seek assistance at their Office. 

strengthen free medical services like free consultation, medicines, dental, laboratory and vaccines by providing the Municipal Health Officer with complete medical facilities and adequate supplies for better delivery of health services to the general public; 

divert portion of the budget of the MSWDO intended for medical assistance to the Municipal Health Office for procurement of medicines and vaccines; and

enter into a Memorandum of Agreement with the service providers for timely rendition of social services to the disadvantaged and marginalized individuals and families.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the Focal Person:
a. Enter into a Purchase Agreements with the PNOs, taking into consideration
the requirements laid down in Item 4.2 and 4.3 of the Deployment Plan;
b. Properly explain to the concerned PNOs that the value of the e-trikes based
on the Property Transfer Report is USD10,249.00 or ₱533,009.49 at the time
of its turnover to the Municipality;
c. Compel the PNOs to submit the requirements enumerated in Item 4.1. of the
Deployment Plan;
d. Designate qualified employees of the Municipality to be the Fleet Manager
and staff, who will be responsible for the overall operation of the program;
e. Collect from the PNOs the applicable contributions to the different funds for
the sustainability of the program;
f. Register the E-Trikes under the name of the Municipality to easily facilitate
the transfer of ownership to the PNOs;
g. Construct the charging station in accordance with the proposal in the
Deployment Plan; and
h. Submit the required reports and notify the DOE in writing of any non-
compliance of the terms as provided for in the Deployment Plan and the Deed
DOD for proper resolution.
